Page Object Model (POM) Design Pattern
--------------------------------

What is the Page Object Model (POM)?

Page Object Model is a design pattern in test automation to create an Object Repository for web UI elements. 
Every web page in the WEB application should have a corresponding page class. 

This Page class will find the WebElements and also may contain page methods which perform operations on those WebElements.

Page Classes (Locators) + Test Cases (Test Scripts)

Benefits of POM 
---------------
Duplication of Code

Code Maintenance

Test cases become short and optimized as you will be able to reuse page object methods in the POM.
